🐳 Q02 — Dockerise Flask App & Push to Docker Hub
🎯 Goal
Run a Flask app inside Docker
Access it in browser
Push image to Docker Hub
🧩 Step 0 — Prerequisites (don’t skip)

Install:

Docker Desktop

After install:

docker --version

✔ Should show version (means Docker is working)

📁 Step 1 — Create project folder
mkdir flask-docker-app
cd flask-docker-app
🧾 Step 2 — Create files

Create 3 files inside folder:

🔹 1. app.py
from flask import Flask
app = Flask(__name__)

@app.route('/')
def home():
    return "Hello from Dockerised Flask!"

if __name__ == '__main__':
    app.run(host='0.0.0.0', port=5000)
🔹 2. requirements.txt
flask
🔹 3. Dockerfile
FROM python:3.11-slim
WORKDIR /app
COPY requirements.txt .
RUN pip install -r requirements.txt
COPY . .
EXPOSE 5000
CMD ["python", "app.py"]
🧠 What Dockerfile does (important for viva)
FROM → base image
WORKDIR → working folder inside container
COPY → copy files
RUN → install dependencies
EXPOSE → open port
CMD → run app
🏗️ Step 3 — Build Docker Image
docker build -t <your-username>/flask-app:latest .

👉 Example:

docker build -t dhanyashriee/flask-app:latest .

✔ This creates your image

▶️ Step 4 — Run container
docker run -d -p 5000:5000 dhanyashriee/flask-app:latest

✔ -p 5000:5000 → maps container port to your system

🌐 Step 5 — Check output

Open browser:

http://localhost:5000

You should see:

Hello from Dockerised Flask!
📦 Step 6 — Push to Docker Hub
🔐 Login
docker login

Enter:

username
password
⬆️ Push image
docker push dhanyashriee/flask-app:latest
🎉 Final Output

✔ Browser shows:

Hello from Dockerised Flask!

✔ Image visible on Docker Hub



-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------
You’ve already done the hard part perfectly 👍 — your push succeeded, so your image is already on Docker Hub. Now you just need to view it in the browser.

🌐 How to see your image on Docker Hub
🟢 Step 1 — Open Docker Hub
Go to:
👉 https://hub.docker.com
(or click Sign in)

🟢 Step 2 — Login
Use your account:


Username: dhanyashriee



🟢 Step 3 — Go to your profile
Click your profile → Repositories
👉 Direct link:
https://hub.docker.com/repositories/dhanyashriee

🟢 Step 4 — Find your image
You should see:
👉 flask-app
Click it.

🟢 Step 5 — Verify image
Inside the repo, you’ll see:


Tag: latest


Size


Pull command:


docker pull dhanyashriee/flask-app:latest

✅ What confirms success
✔ Repository exists
✔ Tag latest is shown
✔ You can see push timestamp
